			<h1 class="site-name p-bg">Sociology</h1>
<a href="http://sociology.about.com/od/M_Index/fl/Macro-and-Microsociology.htm" data-component="spotlight" data-source="spotlight" data-type="image" data-ordinal="1" class="spotlight-image-link"><img src="http://f.tqn.com/y/sociology/1/T/u/5/-/-/GettyImages-508482219.jpg" alt="A man assembles a puzzle of faces, signaling the analytic work done by macro and micro sociologists. - John Lund/Getty Images" width="676" height="437" class="landing-feature spotlight-image" >
</a>        <div class="content">
             <h2 class="heading">
                <a href="http://sociology.about.com/od/M_Index/fl/Macro-and-Microsociology.htm" data-component="spotlight" data-source="spotlight" data-type="spotlight.bestTitle" data-ordinal="1" class="heading-link">What's the Difference Between Macro and Micro Sociology?</a>
             </h2>
<div class="share-options-container open-left with-msg">
<div class="share-btns share-options popout"
data-url="http://sociology.about.com/od/M_Index/fl/Macro-and-Microsociology.htm"
data-social-title="What's the Difference Between Macro and Micro Sociology?"
data-description="Macro- and microsociology have differences in scope, method, and levels of analysis, but both are valuable to the field of sociology, and even complementary."
